---
description: Backend, API, and service-side rules
globs: "app/**/*,api/**/*,backend/**/*,server/**/*,internal/**/*,services/**/*,workers/**/*,jobs/**/*,infra/**/*"
---

- Keep request validation, domain logic, and persistence concerns separated when touching service code.
- Treat public API shapes, CLI interfaces, and message contracts as compatibility boundaries; document breaking changes.
- Prefer explicit error handling, idempotent operations, and safe retry behavior for jobs, queues, and background work.
- When changing data flows, update related tests, fixtures, and operational notes in the same change.
- Follow the project execution, safety, and testing rules in `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md`.

